INSERT INTO public.om_sag_narratives (sag_id, fiscal_year, mission_description, justification, raw_text, source_pdf, source_page_description, source_page_amount, content_hash, ingested_at) VALUES ($$om_comp_5$$, 2026, $$This Budget Activity Group represents approximately one percent of the Combat and Operational Medicine Program budget. It covers the Defense Health
Agency's (DHA) Medical Headquarters and its functions supporting Military Health System's (MHS) worldwide patient care delivery.

Defense Health Agency - Resources required for the DHA operating costs supporting delivery of patient care worldwide for members of the Armed Forces, family
members, and others entitled to Department of War (DoW) health care. Oversees and maintains DoW Unified Medical Program resources for all medical
activities. More specifically, the resources support headquarters functions, including the cost of operating the DHA and centrally managed requirements supporting
the delivery of healthcare services.

Management Headquarters - Required for the DHA management headquarters operating costs, which enable the Agency to coordinate and oversee the
provision of health care within the MHS. Management Headquarters funds will be realigned to the DHA program element in FY 2027 to consolidate operating
costs.

Sexual Assault Prevention - Management Headquarter Activity (MHA) - Resources required for Sexual Assault Prevention efforts related to prevention
strategy development, policy, oversight, research, programs, evaluation, and training for MHA.$$, NULL, NULL, $$Budget J-Books/FY27/MHS/MHS_PB27_J-Book-Vol1-COMP_PSCP.pdf$$, 95, 96, $$7927d46bb046ca763b2ed35819b5b1571ebcc70db7a3e8a6e6fdf7a37c70503f$$, $$2026-05-09T21:43:13.101023+00:00$$) ON CONFLICT DO NOTHING;
