Location/Combat Incentive Pay (Monthly for 210 Personnel)               210              12           $400.00           $1,008,000
                                                                                       Total Lebanon Stipends           $1,008,000

D. IRR

The IRR budget request will fund LSOF training facility modernization and repair. LSOF’s existing training infrastructure is
insufficient to meet training requirements for preparing troops to sustain a persistent ISIS deterrent. Repairing and renovating
facilities will allow LSOF to provide its soldiers the realistic training necessary for successful D-ISIS operations.
Table 21: Lebanon IRR
                                                                   IRR
           Infrastructure Repair and Renovation                     Units                  Cost                 Total Cost Estimate
Improvements to Ranges and Barracks (~ 5 Facilities)                   5                  $200,000                   $1,000,000
                                                                                              Total IRR              $1,000,000

E. SUSTAINMENT

Sustaining CTEF-procured vehicles, facilities, and equipment is critical to ensuring the LSOF retains the capability to conduct D-ISIS
operations. Sustainment funding will support all D-ISIS logistical operations, including supply, services, base operations, and
maintenance. These funds would also ensure repair parts are available for the LAF to maintain full capability. At the same time,
facility sustainment and operating costs include basic provisions required for ongoing operations that enable the enduring defeat of
ISIS.
Table 22: Lebanon Sustainment
